    nar "I open my leaden eyelids and an unfamiliar white seeps into my groggy consciousness. {w}An unfamiliar ceiling is above me."


translate English day2_eda89d3a:


    nar "The white ceiling in question is stained in several places and seems lower than normal. {w}Even with that awareness, it's still completely foreign to me."


translate English day2_b2cc4b4f:


    pl "Morning...?"


translate English day2_c244642d:


    "\n Fragments of broken dreams drift through my still dream-fogged mind before vanishing. {w}I must've slept pretty soundly."


translate English day2_4a278a67:


    "I guess all that walking around I did on my first day had a positive effect on my sleep. {w} Scratching my head, my hair a mess of curls, I take in my surroundings."


translate English day2_02670920:


    "Reality begins dawning on me when I see the pile of clothes that I left scattered on the ground the night before. {w}I should really put my stuff away..."


translate English day2_f5a470c0:


    "As expected, no one came to wake me up. {w}I might have arrived only yesterday, but today is technically my first official day of work."


translate English day2_1cbd0c15:


    et "The situation outside my window looks unchanged from yesterday, {w}enough so that I begin to question the passage of time itself."


translate English day2_76b2fe88_1:


    nvl clear


translate English day2_bd969e5c:


    "\n I have to make sure to lock the door to my room before I leave."


translate English day2_3a6a94e1:


    "The key I was given yesterday is so small that without some way to attach it to myself--like on a cord--the chances of losing it are quite high."


translate English day2_4a3b93a9:


    "As soon as I shut the door to my room, the door next to mine flies open and the disheveled-looking blonde I've come to know fairly well steps out."


translate English day2_4c4ec79e:


    lz2 "[na2]! Morning!"


translate English day2_0218ac68:


    pl "Um?"


