translate English day2_f4dc55f7:


    "Our respective binders are buried among the pile."


translate English day2_87fbabbd:


    et "Each of our files contain a single sheet of paper with a location, date, and simple job description written on it. {w}Seems easy enough."


translate English day2_7ed13394:


    pl "Do you understand any of this, Maya?"


translate English day2_d77738d0:


    my "Mm, for the most part..."


translate English day2_ab348ad7:


    my "It seems like we get a new one of these every day. I wonder who puts them in our folders?"


translate English day2_60601165:


    pl "Who knows? Maybe the bishop?"


translate English day2_ac8f5280:


    my "She's truly amazing...!"


translate English day2_76b2fe88_4:


    nvl clear


translate English day2_b8bcb9e1:


    "\n Nothing bad happened. In the end, we simply psyched ourselves up for nothing. {w}All we had to do was clean up a dirty house."


translate English day2_f0fe4343:


    "I'd be lying if I said I didn't feel nauseated a couple times, but compared to what I dealt with yesterday, it was a breeze."


translate English day2_27bd0593:


    et "Alone with Maya, my thoughts randomly turn back to yesterday."


translate English day2_479dd2fe:



    nvl clear
    "\n Maya is not good at her job--that's simply a fact."


translate English day2_3de963bd:


    "She can sweep the floor, at least, but she's pretty clumsy, {w}and anything more is entirely out of the question."


translate English day2_be2bd5e5:


    "After mopping, she tromps across the still wet floor, leaving messy footprints behind, and has no idea how to wash windows. {w}Having to redo all her work means what should be a simple task takes twice as long. And helping Maya with her tasks means I can't focus on mine."


translate English day2_036164ff:


    et "Her mood quickly turns as gloomy as the weather outside."


translate English day2_f687e66f:


    pl "...Let's head back."


translate English day2_f6309de3:


    my "Huh?"


translate English day2_822f3b4a:


    pl "I don't mind coming back again later on to finish everything up. {w}Besides, it looks like it might rain soon, and I feel bad making you wait."


translate English day2_84a3b380:


    my "I can g-go home by myself, plus... I don't want you to have to come back here twice..."


translate English day2_a47dcf74:


    pl "I don't mind! I was thinking of taking a break anyway. Ready to go?"


translate English day2_6881b38d:


    my "...Okay."


translate English day2_76b2fe88_5:


    nvl clear


translate English day2_bd9f7ee8:


    my "Oh..."


translate English day2_9ce1a30c:


    nar "Thanks to the sudden downpour, the road leading back to the temple is a muddy swamp."


translate English day2_829c1c86:


    nar "The grooves in the road are pretty deep, and I know one wrong step means I'll be drowning in muck. {w}I'm able to make a path through the sludge, but Maya,"


translate English day2_6afdf906:


    nar "who's right behind me, seems stuck, waving her arms frantically in front of her body."


translate English day2_7f10ca3a:


    pl "Are you okay? If you rush, you'll end up planting face-first in the mud, so be careful..."


translate English day2_a5509d83:


    pl "Here, take my hand!"


translate English day2_76b2fe88_6:


    nvl clear


translate English day2_ca9a6efb:


    "\n I take both of her anxious hands in mine. {w}Being so naturally shy, she cries out, her eyes wide in surprise, before squeezing my hand tightly."


translate English day2_80104a69:


    "She's able to force her way forward, with the occasional pause to carefully extract her foot from the sludge."


translate English day2_ddf3d74a:


    "It's because of those ankle boots of hers. {w}There's a reason why folks in the Cleanup crew tend to wear tall, heavier boots."


translate English day2_0f5cd885:


    "It takes a while, but we finally make it safely back to dry ground."


translate English day2_e5d594c2:


    et "Well, more or less. My boots and the hem of my habit are both so caked in mud that it's impossible to shake the grime loose."


translate English day2_76b2fe88_7:


    nvl clear


translate English day2_3334fc23:


    my "..."


translate English day2_2cf5ecb9:


    "\n Maya, who steps onto solid ground a moment after I do, looks pale as a sheet, though I quickly understand why. {w}Her formerly white socks are now stained black with mud, just like mine."


translate English day2_71cf7ccb:


    "It didn't take us that long, but the hand Maya clung to is numb from her death grip. I notice her usually pristine hands are spotted here and there with dirt, thanks to the hard work we were doing earlier. {w}Realizing the same thing, her mouth begins to quiver."


translate English day2_92430422:


    "I'm really sorry, [na2]."


translate English day2_3e8048a2:


    et "And then she apologizes again."


translate English day2_2a7e9afc:



    nvl clear
    "\n It seems like, ever since we came here, all she does is mutter one apology after another. I don't find her annoying or obnoxious in the slightest. {w}But no matter how many times I tell her this, she just ends up apologizing even more."


translate English day2_6f6ed550:


    "It's like each word I say only seems to make her more uncomfortable."


translate English day2_de65d247:


    "All I want in this moment is to hurry back to the temple and rip off my boots, which are filled with dark, black mud."


translate English day2_a243cd79:


    et "But instead, impressed by how hard she tried to keep up with me without giving up, {w}I slow down to match Maya's pace."


translate English day2_76b2fe88_8:


    nvl clear


translate English day2_f9d6a07f:


    nar "We arrive back at the temple to find small groups of people scattered here and there around the main hall."


translate English day2_389de434:


    nar "It's usually filled with folks around now, but for some reason, everyone's focused on the staircase leading up to the second floor."


translate English day2_1a65f1d8:


    "\n I follow their gaze only to immediately stop in my tracks at the sight before me."


translate English day2_fada21a1:


    "Three people, all dressed ridiculously, are descending the staircase, one after the other."


translate English day2_7de74cc3:


    "As soon as the three appear, all the priests in the vicinity place their palms together, bowing in their direction, almost as if dictated to do so."


translate English day2_e40d2c85:


    "Very confused, I glance over at Maya only to find her with her own head bowed in reverence like everyone else."


translate English day2_28545c84:


    "I'm the odd man out. Well, to be fair, that's normal around here. {w}But I go ahead and bow as well, copying the folks around me. I furtively watch their passage out of the corner of my eye."


translate English day2_95e87900:


    "The person in front is the short guy who asked me about my village, followed by the guy who was with Grette, and finally the bishop from the Cleanup Department..."


translate English day2_a5f0cb99:


    et "One, two, three..."


translate English day2_76b2fe88_9:


    nvl clear


translate English day2_b5419542:


    pl "Shouldn't there be one more?"


translate English day2_ddd450d0:


    my "Huh?"


translate English day2_735be423:


    nar "Just as the procession is about to pass us by, I murmur quietly to Maya, head still bowed."


translate English day2_f7e936b5:


    nar "She glances at me before beginning to count on her fingers, still bent at the waist."


translate English day2_d4733c52:


    my "It's probably the bishop from the Academic's Department..."


translate English day2_e0e0ce4f:


    pl "Speaking of which, I don't think I know much about that department."


translate English day2_996bba62:


    my "Ah, they basically decipher ancient texts and research things. Only very smart people are accepted."


translate English day2_0a115393:


    pl "Wow. So that's it, huh?"


translate English day2_7480d2bb:


    my "Yeah..."


translate English day2_ae47a6e2:


    my "Actually, my big sister has always dreamed of getting in, but no matter how hard she studies, it's not enough."


translate English day2_cbf4d739:


    my "Oh! But please don't tell her I told you that. She'll get angry at me again..."


translate English day2_5096f036:


    ex5 "You two from the Disposal Team! Don't just stand there. Go get cleaned up!"


translate English day2_7372d814:


    nar "The priest barks at us as they walk by, reminding us of something that completely slipped both our minds. {w}The mud caked on my pants is a dried-up brick of muck by now."


translate English day2_bc902907:


    nar "I glance over to see Maya looking down at herself, blushing furiously."


translate English day2_dc695041:


    my "U-Um... I'm gonna go on ahead and wash myself off..."


translate English day2_b8adb5f3:


    my "You should hurry up and get changed as well."


translate English day2_bffd05cb:


    pl "Are you heading back early today?"


translate English day2_f69b95e3:


    my "I'm not sure..."


translate English day2_80deb3ba:


    my "I'm sorry, but I really have to go..."


translate English day2_c3e27a58:


    pl "Sure... Be careful on your way back. I'll see you later!"


translate English day2_0aea984d:


    "\n Maya hurries off, but upon realizing she's tracking mud everywhere, slows down as she heads deeper inside the temple."


translate English day2_5ee91033:


    "My opinion of her doesn't change, even if she's dressed in rags and caked in mud, but I can tell she doesn't feel the same way."


translate English day2_6611809c:


    et "The Cleanup Department is the only one with two showers--one in the temple and one in the dorms."


translate English day2_873ba3ca:



    nvl clear
    "\n Perhaps it's just the time of day, but a shower with the only sight being naked male flesh as far as the eye can see is an abomination from any perspective--at least to me. {w}I have no plans on staying long anyway. I'm not a huge fan of how humid it gets in here: the wetness in the air is so oppressive, it makes it hard to breathe."


translate English day2_6010844a:


    "And the faucet doesn't make a lick of sense to me. Either the water's scalding hot or freezing cold, no in-betweens."


translate English day2_295d59aa:


    et "I'm already sick of having to take this many showers."


translate English day2_76b2fe88_10:


    nvl clear


translate English day2_36cda264:


    "\n Having hurried maybe a little too much, I arrive at the cafeteria to find no sight of Maya. {w}The two seniors who'd gone off with her are here, which means she's probably just taking her time."


translate English day2_fee1093e:


    "Standing in the doorway, waves of people move in and out around me."


translate English day2_84ef8ef4:


    "Each time someone sits down, whether alone or in pairs, a musky scent wafts into the air. It's the stench of death, something you can't wash away with soap and water. {w}It's inescapable, enveloping everyone who works here."


translate English day2_01734c0a:


    et "I hear people constantly say they'll never get used to it, and yet it seems that they have. {w}I personally can't stand it, but this discomfort has already become part of my daily life."


translate English day2_58e169bc:



    nvl clear
    "\n Maya's face naturally surfaces from my jumble of thoughts."


translate English day2_5e1c5afa:


    "I remember how she looked in her muddy boots, her skirt an embarrassing, wrinkled, sullied mess. I can't help but worry about her, enough so that it's kind of comical."


translate English day2_7227738a:


    "She must smile sometimes, right? It seems like an obvious fact, but the only image my mind can conjure up is of her bowing, her face a mask of misery. {w}The picture of her that sprang to mind gradually begins to solidify. She's still nowhere to be seen."


translate English day2_afc041b8:


    "I have a strong hunch that Maya's probably skipping dinner tonight, and so I hurry to grab some bread for myself before it runs out."


translate English day2_8efe9e6f:


    "I guess a part of me misses her, though I don't really know why. And I can't seem to escape the putrid scent that lingers in the air, clinging to the tip of my nose."


translate English day2_f090ad44:


    et "I should really study the floor plan of the temple so I don't get lost anymore."


translate English day2_my_32629f4a:


    nar "Walking out into the yard, I see a familiar figure. Maya's sitting on the bench, hugging her knees to herself."


translate English day2_my_d1c7ba57:


    nar "Before I can call out to her, the sound of pebbles crunching under my shoes gives me away. {w}She immediately winces in fear while turning in my direction."


translate English day2_my_b53bcb44:


    nar "Just as surprised as she is, I raise both hands out in front of me, as if to show I'm unarmed and perfectly safe. {w}The look of fear in her eyes immediately softens once she sees me."


translate English day2_my_93446af6:


    nar "Seeing her is comforting for some reason."


translate English day2_my_f97a3f70:


    pl "Maya! I was wondering what I'd do if you weren't here. Did you eat already?"


translate English day2_my_68f07346:


    my "Nope, my sisters aren't around today, plus... I don't have much of an appetite today..."


translate English day2_my_d773ba18:


    pl "You sure?"


translate English day2_my_ed2b2c3d:


    my "Yeah, it's fine. I'm used to it..."


translate English day2_my_79931dde:


    nar "From the way she's talking, I guess this kind of thing happens often."


translate English day2_my_38a48dd3:


    nar "Instead of an answer, I offer her some of the bread I brought from the cafeteria."


translate English day2_my_251f22aa:


    nar "Made from local ingredients, there is still a faint smell of warm butter from the bread roll."


translate English day2_my_063f50e1:


    nar "Her eyes widen in surprise again, but this time, I notice her body trembling faintly."


translate English day2_my_d3ad97f8:


    my "You brought this... for me?"


translate English day2_my_2ea1c79c:


    pl "Well... I had a feeling you probably skipped dinner, so..."


translate English day2_my_0c388a57:


    pl "Well, I brought a couple so I could eat out here, too. It's better than going hungry!"


translate English day2_my_3334fc23:


    my "..."


translate English day2_my_8d4622df:


    nar "Her hand hovers uncertainly for a moment before she takes one of the rolls."


translate English day2_my_4aeaa9ff:


    nar "I can't help but feel sorry for her as she nibbles at it, though Maya seems more relaxed, no longer curled up into a stiff ball."


translate English day2_my_ba00812a:


    nar "I sit down next to her, glancing absent-mindedly around the garden."


translate English day2_my_108d2dac:


    nar " It's almost definitely a garden, although not very conspicuous, mostly containing rambling roses."


translate English day2_my_ec50d155:


    nar "The sight of the bright red blossoms blooming all over the curved archway is fairly lackluster,"


translate English day2_my_9f623287:


    nar "probably thanks to the abundance of wilted petals, likely from neglect."


translate English day2_my_35c461e2:


    nar "I remember how out of place it seemed the first time I found it; {w}Such a beautiful spot buried away right next to the Cleanup Department..."


translate English day2_my_611626e3:


    nar "and yet the gloom that pervades the office feels entwined between the neglected roses."


translate English day2_my_83a374db:


    nar "What seems to catch Maya's attention isn't the roses in full bloom or the archway itself."


translate English day2_my_1f51f9e7:


    nar "It's this bit of dirt between the bricks where small flower buds are just beginning to sprout, so small you have to squint to see them."


translate English day2_my_18656d6a:


    nar "Well, sitting here, I can tell why this is her favorite bench. {w}You can see the buds better from this spot."


translate English day2_my_b74efee9:


    nar "She seems happier than usual, watching her favorite budding blossoms, {w}looking so much more like weeds than the gorgeous flowers they'll eventually become."


translate English day2_my_bb88a8ff:


    pl "You don't get along with your sister, huh?"


translate English day2_my_1cf08c9c:


    my "Pardon me...?"


translate English day2_my_9ede34b3:


    my "Wh-Why do you say that?"


translate English day2_my_9e74ee4b:


    nar "Her expression immediately stiffens. I have no intention of picking on her--quite the opposite."


translate English day2_my_3d4cf24f:


    pl "Well, the reason why is..."


translate English day2_my_c3705621:


    pl "I noticed she basically ignored you yesterday and she didn't offer to help you out at all, despite being way more experienced."


translate English day2_my_e5fc7ad5:


    pl "And, I mean, look at you. You're here all by yourself, right?"


translate English day2_my_be41fd3a:


    pl "I don't mean to stick my nose into your family business, but it's hard for me to just sit back and watch."


translate English day2_my_54b3a2b7:


    my "No, it's fine, and... I know how it looks."


translate English day2_my_4a01efaf:


    my "The thing about my older sister is that she tends to worry a lot. But I swear she's a good person, and she's actually taught me so much."


translate English day2_my_5f6a144d:


    my "The reason why she's so cold sometimes is because she's sick of me being a good-for-nothing pain in the butt..."


translate English day2_my_4f0b9275:


    my "I mean, I would be too..."


translate English day2_my_3163a651:


    pl "..."


translate English day2_my_19608978:


    my "Also... I can tell you're really worried about me, [na2]."


translate English day2_my_24a91037:


    pl "Huh? No, I mean... anyone would be worried about someone who always seems so sad all the time, right?"


translate English day2_my_b6ac1079:


    my "Yeah... I guess so."


translate English day2_my_39dcbfba:


    my "I'm sorry for making you worry. You really don't have to..."


translate English day2_my_ec3e9911:


    nar "So here's what I'm thinking."


translate English day2_my_7bb1b85a:


    nar "If I felt things were more awkward between us, the best thing would be for me to tell this mud-covered girl, \"I know, but I do anyway.\""


translate English day2_my_ad4a3c4b:


    nar "I'm assuming the reason why she doesn't believe me is because I'm always giving her vague responses with my true feelings mixed in."


translate English day2_my_7951d5c9:


    pl "You don't have to apologize all the time."


translate English day2_my_7a0bd95a:


    pl "I don't know what other people think, but..."


translate English day2_my_227a3aef:


    pl "I swear that you've never bothered me in the slightest. Plus, I know how much you put into your work every single time."


translate English day2_my_4ab72669:


    pl "If anything, seeing you struggle just makes me want to help you more, which is why you don't need to apologize to me."


translate English day2_my_92bef27e:


    nar "Even after giving it some thought, I still find myself at an ambiguous impasse. Besides, I feel like I'll just sound crazy if I say what I'm thinking aloud."


translate English day2_my_20493113:


    nar "As the silence deepens, regret washes over me."


translate English day2_my_60661c2a:


    my "You're so strange..."


translate English day2_my_6bc2cff2:


    my "I know how boring it is to be with me and yet... well, you've stuck by my side this whole time, so you should know better than anyone."


translate English day2_my_ec928bbb:


    my "No one's ever said anything like that to me before."


translate English day2_my_c8473d28:


    my "You're really weird, [na2]."


translate English day2_my_d3413beb:


    pl "Uh..."


translate English day2_my_7cdc3aae:


    pl "I'm not weird. It's the people you surround yourself with who are the real weirdos. Blatantly giving someone the silent treatment like that... I don't think it's very nice."


translate English day2_my_3334fc23_1:


    my "..."


translate English day2_my_758fc3ad:


    nar "Whoops. No matter how much I don't get her older sister, she's still Maya's family. She must feel pretty uncomfortable having me bad mouth her own family in front of her."


translate English day2_my_5c444e59:


    pl "Uh, sorry. I didn't mean for it to come out like that..."


translate English day2_my_a787ad1d:


    my "...It's okay."


translate English day2_my_55dc03ed:


    nar "Followed by the tiniest sliver of a voice, almost too faint to hear."


translate English day2_my_87afd41b:


    my "Thank you for caring about me... "


translate English day2_my_464f855e:


    extend "Think I should say something next time?"


translate English day2_my_f1ca2597:


    pl "Huh? Well... yeah. Seems like the much better strategy, in my opinion."


translate English day2_my_edaef2f4:


    nar "The corners of her mouth just barely curl up into a faint smile, though there's no joy in it."


translate English day2_my_540a28cc:


    nar "She looks different than how I remember--a smoldering, empty husk of her usual self."


translate English day2_my_54df6f58:


    nar "Maybe because this isn't how Maya really feels, or maybe that she's not as happy as I thought she was."


translate English day2_my_75c0c039:


    nar "Regardless, I'll never be able to forget that subtle gesture that didn't seem like a smile at all."


translate English day2_rs_6f1fb902:


    "\n Behind one of the dormitories filling out the temple's majestic silhouette is a cute, little building I've never been inside."


translate English day2_rs_a603280b:


    "I've been curious about it since yesterday, but it was one of those places I didn't feel like checking out."


translate English day2_rs_29a726c2:


    "Keeping an open mind, I enter, but it's so quiet inside that I almost get discouraged and leave."


translate English day2_rs_6fc61289:


    "The oily scent specific to wood drifts about. Did everyone here leave for lunch?"


translate English day2_rs_1fcfe5c5:


    et "My gaze turns to the staircase at the end of the hallway, thinking maybe they're below."


translate English day2_rs_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day2_rs_ae9ba4c7:


    "\n The stairs appear to lead underground, but there are no markers or doors to be found. I can't get a feel for how far down they go, but the stairwell is illuminated here and there."


translate English day2_rs_144ee54a:


    "That fact means an outsider like me is allowed to enter; I know because I'm familiar with places like these."


translate English day2_rs_cb3f85fa:


    "The further down I go, the less I can smell that distinct, woody scent. Instead, my nose starts to detect something like a flower being burned as incense."


translate English day2_rs_ad97ccf8:


    "I think it's one I've smelled before, so for a moment, it sets my mind at ease. But the further down I go, the thicker the scent becomes, causing my head to hurt."


translate English day2_rs_d8468ad0:


    et "The sight I eventually reach, though, is so magnificent that the smell doesn't seem to matter anymore. Books--so many books, more than I can count--are packed onto every single wall and bookshelf."


translate English day2_rs_97c97e3c:



    nvl clear
    "\n I'm surprised by how large the space is considering it's underground. I look up. The spiral staircase I descended goes up very, very high. As it turns out, this cute little building is actually a library."


translate English day2_rs_9eaf4cca:


    "\"Wow, this is amazing, but...\""


translate English day2_rs_0986b3bf:


    "Something's strange about it. Libraries usually soothe the soul, but this one just feels wrong."


translate English day2_rs_0eda861b:


    "And it's not just the entrance, the staircase, and the library proper, but the fact that I haven't seen a single person since coming into the building. That's not natural, is it?"


translate English day2_rs_53b630c4:


    "My muttered remark dissipates in the vast room, gone forever. I seem to be alone, but this whole time, I could sense that someone's here. That's definitely creeping me out."


translate English day2_rs_805f5148:


    et "Is someone hiding out, watching me? Maybe an unimaginably large group of people?"


translate English day2_rs_76b2fe88_1:


    nvl clear


translate English day2_rs_78d378ef:


    qus "Are you looking for any book in particular?"


translate English day2_rs_2e1e0f44:


    nar "But as I'm standing there vacantly, a woman suddenly casts a shadow over me."


translate English day2_rs_3c661648:


    nar "She's a young woman with skin as white as snow and all kinds of equipment on. She's pretty tall, too, which makes her seem strangely intimidating."


translate English day2_rs_22117729:


    pl "Huh...? Oh, no, not exactly. I don't read much..."


translate English day2_rs_7235d70f:


    nar "I can smell the flower scent from her even more strongly now. It's sweet and powerful enough to immediately distract me from my thoughts."


translate English day2_rs_32f131ee:


    nar "Unlike the scents in the Cleanup Department, which had a bunch of things mixed together, this one was artificial--pure and intense."


translate English day2_rs_07f23b65:


    nar "I actually feel like I might faint, so I take a deep breath and snap myself out of it."


translate English day2_rs_cff72301:


    nar "I shake my head, which prompts a smile from the woman, who is wearing purple lipstick; I guess it was pretty funny to watch me."


translate English day2_rs_1eafc4e0:


    pl "I was just kind of impressed. I can't believe every little thing I can see packed into here is a book."


translate English day2_rs_f1467268:


    pl "Are you the librarian here, miss?"


translate English day2_rs_72f27709:


    ev_q "Oh, well... Heh heh... Something like that, anyway. At the very least, all of the books here are certainly within my purview..."


translate English day2_rs_4c503872:


    nar "She slowly twists her body to give me a good view of the inundation of books. The sight seeps into my mind before my senses pick it up."


translate English day2_rs_2b7148b4:


    ev_q "Hee hee. This whole place is the culmination of over a millenium of history."


translate English day2_rs_0994af53:


    ev_q "Something humans have been building up, so to speak, for a long time..."


translate English day2_rs_2f34a3b3:


    ev_q "You can think of it all as... encounters, between man and history, between history and history, and between man and divinity."


translate English day2_rs_ba1ada76:


    pl "Kind of sounds like something I heard this morning..."


translate English day2_rs_bb41fb42:


    pl "How can objects created by people be connected to God?"


translate English day2_rs_847f558b:


    ev_q "Man's history consists of ties between people, like knots in rope. "


translate English day2_rs_559747bd:


    ev_q "Our god is the one who ties those knots. "


translate English day2_rs_06a52b9f:


    ev_q "After all, it is impossible for the likes of man to attain knowledge outside his awareness with only his own strength..."


translate English day2_rs_e877223c:


    pl "Huh... I see. Am I allowed to be in here without asking?"


translate English day2_rs_9375f839:


    ev_q "Yes, of course. We welcome all to this place: our lovely siblings, the birds perched on the windowsill, and even the scent of irises heralding summer..."


translate English day2_rs_6e0de91a:


    pl "Oh... So *that* was the floral scent."


translate English day2_rs_2054e7d7:


    ev_q "That's right. Isn't it elegant? I received the flowers as a gift, so I used them to create perfume."


translate English day2_rs_6ae9b70a:


    ev_q "If you've taken a liking to it, I can give you a bottle."


translate English day2_rs_abe61d8b:


    nar "She takes a small purple bottle out of an inside pocket, then smoothly places it into my hands."


translate English day2_rs_2d012995:


    pl "Whoa...! Uh, thanks for this."


translate English day2_rs_87cf7681:


    pl "Would you mind if I looked around a little more?"


translate English day2_rs_41f2b3b2:


    ev_q "Heh heh... No, of course not..."


translate English day2_rs_6b80a580:


    ev_q "But be careful. The place is sure to confuse and lead astray..."


translate English day2_rs_10328ef1:


    nar "With that mysterious comment, the \"librarian\" turns and walks away, the soft hem of her skirt fluttering."


translate English day2_rs_06cb6edf:


    nar "She moves into a complicated array of wall-like bookshelves with innumerable books on them. And just like that, she disappears from sight."


translate English day2_rs_359964de:


    nar "Snapping myself out of my daze, I go to take a step. When I do, I lose my balance and almost topple over. "


translate English day2_rs_42bdccf7:


    nar "Am I drunk on that perfume or something? I have no idea, but I manage to get my feet to walk properly this time."


translate English day2_rs_2f06fb4a:


    nar "This huge place is reaking havoc with my inquisitiveness and need to explore. I have permission to look around more on my own."


translate English day2_rs_918bfab3:


    nar " And I do, wandering this way and that, until eventually I come to a door in the back."


translate English day2_rs_fa116e71:


    nar "I look around again; there are other doors like it nearby. I pick one and knock twice."


translate English day2_rs_e75d64a1:


    nar "And then..."


translate English day2_rs_b98ac7a9:


    pl "Whoa! You scared me!" with sshake


translate English day2_rs_0bba3600:


    pl "What was that for? You should be more careful when leaving rooms!"


translate English day2_rs_e17f9f9f:


    nar "Just as I knocked, the door clattered open and a person came bursting out."


translate English day2_rs_6269f8b1:


    nar "She has distinct hair--it's short, and vividly pink. She's a little tall for a girl, though she'd be a little short for a guy. "


translate English day2_rs_18e3f492:


    nar "Either way, everything about her appearance was pretty much normal. She looked at me, her black eyes going wide."


translate English day2_rs_6dfeb882:


    qus "......"


translate English day2_rs_7c0a228b:


    pl "Who are you? Are you here to read, too?"


translate English day2_rs_6dfeb882_1:


    qus "......"


translate English day2_rs_14be2744:


    pl "Can't you hear me...? What's your name?"


translate English day2_rs_c095e860:


    qus "My... name...?"


translate English day2_rs_c2f63f70:


    rs "My name is Rose."


translate English day2_rs_332ef2a6:


    nar "The mystery girl answers softly but clearly, then suddenly freezes. Her eyes go wide like she's surprised about something."


translate English day2_rs_41749628:


    rs "You shouldn't be here."


translate English day2_rs_ee408906:


    pl "Huh?"


translate English day2_rs_bd2a65e7:


    rs "My name is Rose."


translate English day2_rs_b883b4ff:


    rs "Bye-bye."


translate English day2_rs_4aba9f0c:


    pl "Wait. Huh? Uh, bye..."


translate English day2_rs_8393cccb:


    nar "What happened next happened very quickly."


translate English day2_rs_81610b24:


    nar "The child named Rose takes a few steps back, her hand still on the door handle, then waves good-bye to me and shuts the door."


translate English day2_rs_b6a6a44e:


    nar "I've been driven out. I try to get a peek inside to settle this inexplicable feeling, but the door shows no signs of opening back up at this point."


translate English day2_ar_d9305a89:


    "\n If this temple is known for anything, you'd think it'd be known for being a tall enough building that you can see it from anywhere in the capital."


translate English day2_ar_0eea7757:


    "But even this temple features one building that stands out in particular."


translate English day2_ar_e4f1bdbd:


    "A building of an almost arrogant construction makes the temple's silhouette stand out even more."


translate English day2_ar_7d13f391:


    "Even without any knowledge of the capital, I can tell at a glance that it's home to the Magic Department."


translate English day2_ar_94e9c1a4:


    "\"The Magic Department...\""


translate English day2_ar_bc9566fd:


    "How many times has that mysterious group tripped me up since I got here?"


translate English day2_ar_3c308f7c:


    et "The doors of the building are dismal, yet flowery. For a moment, I hesitate to enter. But then, praying the truth lies behind these doors, I push them open."


translate English day2_ar_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day2_ar_f3a6070a:


    "\n Inside, it is undeniably the very pride of the capital."


translate English day2_ar_e594604a:


    "The ceiling is high, and glistens in a golden color like that of a wheat field heralding the coming autumn. Pure white pillars reach up to it as if to provide support for the descending light."


translate English day2_ar_29746ade:


    "The light from the sun, shining from behind the clouds in the sky, simply illuminates this space."


translate English day2_ar_04eda82a:


    "I haven't seen the sun since coming to the capital--but it seems to still light up this place alone."


translate English day2_ar_51a38b1a:


    "That's not the only thing that surprises me. If my eyes are still functioning properly, the people here are all doing some kind of training."


translate English day2_ar_34008ac9:


    "But not a moment after I sigh aloud at the extravagant sight, I look directly ahead and freeze."


translate English day2_ar_c1dacebd:


    et "All of the people have stopped to look at me."


translate English day2_ar_fb445a78:



    nvl clear
    "\n They all have black hair and wear the same clothing. "


translate English day2_ar_1d1669a8:


    "They also hide their faces with a black cloth in the same way. Every single one of them--and there are enough to fill this vast area--looks exactly the same."


translate English day2_ar_4ac53342:


    et "They all whisper among themselves as I stand there awkwardly. The coincidental disturbance ripples through them, quickly filling the room."


translate English day2_ar_76b2fe88_1:


    nvl clear


translate English day2_ar_18d92379:


    qus "Okay, everyone, quiet!"


translate English day2_ar_2967c087:


    nar "An especially tall man claps several times, then walks over to me."


translate English day2_ar_8e320667:


    nar "He looks completely different from the others here. Instead of black clothing, his is white with gold accents and accessories."


translate English day2_ar_acfa5098:


    nar "Everything about his appearance is so overdone that I can't even tell where that soft metallic noise is coming from every time he takes a step."


translate English day2_ar_b0ee728c:


    qus "Heya. What did you need? This building belongs to the Magic Department, so it's supposed to be forbidden to outsiders and all that."


translate English day2_ar_ec85e946:


    pl "You're telling me this stuffy place is only for the Magic Department??"


translate English day2_ar_c72f0950:


    en_q "How rude! Magicians have always needed to train in fields other than magic." with sshake


translate English day2_ar_13b2fae0:


    en_q "If you don't have a good reason for waltzing in here and interfering with our training, then we'll be checking your identification and sending you right back!"


translate English day2_ar_6ae61972:


    qus "Enoch! He is not at fault--you are the one being rude! Will you not watch your tongue before an honored guest?!"


translate English day2_ar_e6ae0dbd:


    nar "A new voice rings out clearly in this large room. I don't need to look around for its owner--I find her right away."


translate English day2_ar_b8fe8835:


    nar "Although the people in the room all stopped and clearly acted wary of me, they now hurried to part to the sides. "


translate English day2_ar_28c4c1e0:


    nar "As they do, I see her in the middle."


translate English day2_ar_c1350a40:


    nar "She has black hair and white clothing with golden decorations. She basically looks exactly like the man before; nothing about her particularly stands out."


translate English day2_ar_bfddcdf8:


    nar "However, she has a commanding presence in spite of her appearance, not because of it. That sets her apart from the rest of the people here."


translate English day2_ar_35cc532c:


    nar "In many ways, she reminds me of the sunrise."


translate English day2_ar_0b21c72a:


    nar "My initial impression of her entrance might be simple, but that's what I think when I see the light that has reflected off the ceiling and descended now floating around her."


translate English day2_ar_a3ae1c2d:


    nar "Her vivid blue eyes shine like perfectly clear, serene skies--the kind I can't see anymore in this dark, dismal place."


translate English day2_ar_dda60252:


    ar_q "Your appearance must make you Lord [na], yes? We've been waiting for you."


translate English day2_ar_7f545b41:


    en_q "S-Sister...!"


translate English day2_ar_c245d177:


    ar_q "You would still argue your point, Enoch?"


translate English day2_ar_18f48adb:


    ar_q "And what is the meaning of you not knowing his face when you were the one who first tracked him down?"


translate English day2_ar_ee03a8db:


    en_q "Well, I... I apologize."


translate English day2_ar_b6d4ddb6:


    pl "Hey, wait a sec, will you? I'd like to get in a word here, if I could." with sshake


translate English day2_ar_35d59990:


    ar_q "My apologies, sir. Such was not our intent..."


translate English day2_ar_4dcd9a80:


    ar_q "If anything is unclear to you, please ask."


translate English day2_ar_1fb39a5d:


    pl "Huh... Well, I've got a lot I want to ask. But could we do introductions first?"


translate English day2_ar_c0a093ab:


    nar "The dozens of people watching me flinch in surprise."


translate English day2_ar_a548c664:


    nar "Apparently something I said is pretty unheard of in the capital."


translate English day2_ar_c80b240b:


    nar "It causes a small stir to spread, igniting like a lit candle, then throwing the surroundings into confusion."


translate English day2_ar_67ef35fa:


    ar_q "What are you all standing around for when a guest is here? Clear the way!"


translate English day2_ar_7abb1fa4:


    nar "But the one at the center of the confusion continues to stand upright, once again opening a path."


translate English day2_ar_4f019277:


    nar "Then she gazes at me. Her eyes hold no fear, but I give a start at the control she's exerting over this place."


translate English day2_ar_3bd287f2:


    ar_q "I am embarrassed to say we are not yet prepared for you... But for now, please come this way. I will hear your questions there."


translate English day2_ar_c301c9a4:


    pl "R-Right..."


translate English day2_ar_821031ef:


    nar "I'm not sure why yet, but she seems quite welcoming of my visit. "


translate English day2_ar_5ff51b2f:


    nar "The others echo my thoughts--why would she be so polite to someone who barged in like I did?"


translate English day2_ar_75ac302e:


    nar "The room she brings me to is a warm, comfy one with a fluffy sofa in it, "


translate English day2_ar_38855d5f:


    nar "but I can't really be at ease with her presence here."


translate English day2_ar_a278eef3:


    nar "She takes a seat across from me, with the man from before standing beside her. He still seems unhappy about the situation overall."


translate English day2_ar_9e079175:


    ar_q "Ahem. Please allow me to introduce myself."


translate English day2_ar_db71fda7:


    ar "I am Arne Alternata, eldest daughter of House Alternata and an auxiliary bishop of the Magic Department."


translate English day2_ar_b90869b9:


    ar "I have heard much about you from my uncle."


translate English day2_ar_92c787f0:


    pl "Your uncle...?"


translate English day2_ar_78db3531:


    ar "Was there a black-haired boy, short of stature, in your village, Brother?"


translate English day2_ar_94fc5a10:


    pl "Oh!"


translate English day2_ar_227a8b52:


    ar "Certain circumstances have forced him to remain young... "


translate English day2_ar_3f38571d:


    ar "But that man is both my uncle and the current bishop of the Magic Department, Erzsebet Alternata."


translate English day2_ar_5140f9ce:


    pl "That's a pretty long name..."


translate English day2_ar_f7f299b7:


    en_q "House Alternata is pretty much the most famous magic family out there, you know. You must really be from the total boonies if you didn't know that..."


translate English day2_ar_66838a34:


    ar "Did I not tell you to watch your tongue? Go wait for us outside."


translate English day2_ar_fcb3863c:


    en_q "Ngh..."


translate English day2_ar_6f98b201:


    en_q "I'm sure you've got important stuff to talk to our guest about... But we're in the middle of training, so please don't draw this out, Sister..."


translate English day2_ar_43001988:


    nar "The man freezes at her barbed comment for a moment, but then assumes an orderly expression as he looks between the two of us."


translate English day2_ar_d68db286:


    nar "But that's all. He then simply nods and exits the room, apparently not willing to object any further."


translate English day2_ar_56896b44:


    ar "My word... It's quite noisy outside, though I suppose it always is at this time."


translate English day2_ar_b0bab5bb:


    nar "She sighs, watching to make sure the door closes all the way."


translate English day2_ar_c6e3cdf3:


    nar "At first I think she's lamenting the current situation, but her expression is now more peaceful than it has been."


translate English day2_ar_5ad6df3b:


    nar "With that, I'm able to face this Arne Alternata woman without distractions."


translate English day2_ar_eae1abed:


    ar "He is Enoch Apis, another auxiliary member of the Magic Department who protects the bishop."


translate English day2_ar_9215e5f4:


    ar "He is not related by blood, but I was raised with him from a young age. I consider him my younger stepbrother."


translate English day2_ar_8dd8b018:


    ar "Despite his earlier behavior, he is generally docile and dependable... And as his stepsister, I would like to apologize in his place for his rudeness."


translate English day2_ar_3880a988:


    pl "Hey, I really don't mind it much. Don't worry about it."


translate English day2_ar_1b9a115e:


    pl "Still, though... You're family, huh? I was thinking you seemed kind of alike. You seem to get along well."


translate English day2_ar_41c71717:


    ar "This temple is home to several departments, but the Magic Department differs somewhat from the rest."


translate English day2_ar_bdc03c37:


    ar "They have all built up familial bonds with one another. The fact that I am able stand before them and lead them, if only in minor aspects, is also a source of pride for me."


translate English day2_ar_d9b1b6db:


    ar "As you are soon to join us, Brother [na]... I would like you to feel at ease in regards to speaking with me."


translate English day2_ar_4712872b:


    pl "Oh, right. That reminds me. I wanted to get some more details on all this, if I could."


translate English day2_ar_c9c44596:


    ar "Yes, I'm sure. The truth is that we had planned for my uncle to directly call you here, then talk to you himself, but..."


translate English day2_ar_241ca71e:


    ar "Unfortunately, he has not been able to spare the time for these past few days."


translate English day2_ar_945ae156:


    ar " It pains me to place the burden on you instead, "


translate English day2_ar_a0c6a3ee:


    ar "but would you be able to stop by here tomorrow afternoon? I will tell my uncle in the meantime."


translate English day2_ar_a6929678:


    pl "Tomorrow afternoon? Okay, gotcha. I'm fine with that. I don't have much to do after work's done anyway."


translate English day2_ar_a36e0812:


    ar "You show us such generosity, despite us having worsened your mood due to our lack of consideration... "


translate English day2_ar_dd90e09f:


    ar "I cannot apologize to you enough."


translate English day2_ar_057c8534:


    pl "Hey, seriously, no worries! I said I really don't mind!"


translate English day2_ar_f806eb4f:


    nar "I think I finally know why that man visited me out of the blue. "


translate English day2_ar_e50d7375:


    nar "The culture of this Magic Department is so similar to that of my home village that it makes me uncomfortable."


translate English day2_ar_726ad804:


    nar "Did I finally escape that group only to end up falling in with this circle?"


translate English day2_ar_dbf4d7c1:


    ar "...Brother? You seem quite worried. What is it?"


translate English day2_ar_2d014fd1:


    pl "Hrm... Well, it's just, the whole \"Brother\" thing seems a little stiff and formal to me."


translate English day2_ar_2b9fedd6:


    pl "We're supposed to be forming a bond anyway, right? Why not just call me [na2]?"


translate English day2_ar_402e66f0:


    ar "[na2]... Does that name hold some sort of meaning?"


translate English day2_ar_a42de0e4:


    pl "Nah, not really. It's just like a nickname, I guess. Everyone in my family called me that too."


translate English day2_ar_2c498f7c:


    ar "A nickname... I see. A very good custom, indeed. If it wouldn't be rude, may I also refer to you as such?"


translate English day2_ar_291ed92f:


    pl "Sure! And since your name is Arne..."


translate English day2_ar_e2c7dc54:


    pl "Why don't I call you Arnie?"


translate English day2_ar_2f3fff42:


    ar "Heh heh. That's the first time anyone has ever referred to me like that."


translate English day2_ar_133fa4b6:


    ar "So this is how it feels... I will treasure this name you have bestowed upon me, Brother [na2]. I thank you from the bottom of my heart."


translate English day2_ar_852d5960:


    pl "Still feels weird being called that, but... Eh, whatever. It's fine for now. "


translate English day2_ar_987de05e:


    pl "It's nice to meet you, Arnie."


translate English day2_ar_1f048be4:


    ar "The pleasure is all mine. Truly."


translate English day2_ar_f45650aa:


    ar "...Oh, and if you are heading back, allow me to assign you an escort--"


translate English day2_ar_dbca528e:


    pl "Like I said, I'm fine!"


translate English day2_gr_3a6e311d:


    nar "Thankfully, my memories from yesterday haven't led me astray. The infirmary is located down from the central lobby and around the corner."


translate English day2_gr_d738871c:


    nar "The cheerful atmosphere that only seems to exist here feels warmer, in part because I've been outside in the cold for so long."


translate English day2_gr_07811e56:


    nar "Still, everything seems slightly different. There's a rather large stack of boxes near the door, and as I enter, I see Dr. Grette carrying in more of them."


translate English day2_gr_28b926df:


    gr "My oh my! If it isn't [na2]! Could you be a dear and wait just a moment? I've got my hands full..."


translate English day2_gr_67d4ab95:


    pl "Want some help?"


translate English day2_gr_5d2ca79a:


    gr "You don't mind? That'd be great!"


translate English day2_gr_7d88ccb1:


    gr "Here... Oof! These are pretty heavy, so don't hurt yourself!"


translate English day2_gr_f3c0566d:


    pl "I should be able to handle this much at least."


translate English day2_gr_9348123a:


    nar "Rolling up my sleeves, I hoist one of the boxes up off the ground."


translate English day2_gr_7c098f95:


    nar "Some boxes are lighter than others, though the heaviest I can't lift without supporting part of it on one knee."


translate English day2_gr_4df6c24d:


    nar "She'd planned on leaving the boxes on and around the nearby shelf, but with my help and being so fired up, we're able to get everything put away in their rightful spot quickly."


translate English day2_gr_20a826c5:


    nar "She's quite the sight, standing on tiptoe, her slender arms trembling as she tries to place a box on a shelf that's almost juuust out of reach."


translate English day2_gr_bb8233ff:


    nar "She's the type of person you can't take your eyes off of--in more ways than one."


translate English day2_gr_3ce9317f:


    gr "Whew! I couldn't have done it without you! "


translate English day2_gr_8fad0d08:


    gr "I could've easily lifted one or two of these boxes by myself when I was younger, but those days are long behind me..."


translate English day2_gr_6b166f93:


    pl "Oh, come on... Don't be so hard on yourself."


translate English day2_gr_df402d7e:


    gr "Heh heh heh! My, my! Looks like my secret's come out!"


translate English day2_gr_1a47961d:


    gr "Despite my appearance, I'm basically the custodian around here. What kind of host am I, making my guests do my work for me."


translate English day2_gr_95307aeb:


    gr "Go on and make yourself at home! I've got a tray of cookies today."


translate English day2_gr_0d2822bc:


    pl "Ooh! I appreciate the hospitality. And these cookies look great!"


translate English day2_gr_c766d1dc:


    pl "What are you doing with all these boxes anyway? Isn't this the infirmary?"


translate English day2_gr_3dd54d59:


    gr "Ah, it's just some supplies. Stuff like the toothbrushes you guys use, masks, and underwear. {w}When folks around here run out of daily necessities, they can swing by and grab some."


translate English day2_gr_d7f7a3b0:


    gr "I also have some other priests running medicine and bandages to the sick ward, too."


translate English day2_gr_a0423eaa:


    gr "Normally the bishop helps me with that, but they're busy today."


translate English day2_gr_4275a9fa:


    pl "I saw him this morning. The guy with the glasses, right?"


translate English day2_gr_59269237:


    gr "That's him! With his hair all done up, he looks like a different person. If only he cared about his appearance more often..."


translate English day2_gr_609b38be:


    gr "Oh! And worked on his posture!"


translate English day2_gr_5cde96a8:


    pl "Uh-huh... Oh, right. There's something I wanted to ask you."


translate English day2_gr_cfa9b604:


    gr "And what might that be, [na2]?"


translate English day2_gr_95a8ea70:


    pl "What exactly is an auxillary bishop?"


translate English day2_gr_dfc34c83:


    gr "My, my! They didn't tell you?"


translate English day2_gr_9024db11:


    gr "Hrm... So, for example, you know how trainees like yourself can become priests after their probationary period is over?"


translate English day2_gr_cf7cbe69:


    gr "Auxillary bishops are a step up from that. They basically act like assistants to the bishops above them."


translate English day2_gr_780d6790:


    gr "Not only do they keep the bishop safe, but they help them with work and manage the department in their place when necessary... Yep, something like that."


translate English day2_gr_3f6636cd:


    pl "Ho ho! Then you're an auxillary bishop, as well?"


translate English day2_gr_2ad7dfb7:


    gr "Winner winner, chicken dinner! I'm Grette, the Health Department's auxillary bishop. Heh heh! I'm not actually the custodian."


translate English day2_gr_bf6d0b74:


    pl "Wow! Then those weird clothes are a perk of being the bishop's assistant?"


translate English day2_gr_1dcbf9e2:


    gr "Nope, not exactly. Once you're baptized and become an official priest, you can order special vestments that visually designate your stigmata."


translate English day2_gr_6236d339:


    pl "What do you mean?"


translate English day2_gr_4928dfdd:


    gr "Well... Basically, it's like this. Stigmata are a fundamental part of our divine power,"


translate English day2_gr_b5df4910:


    gr "and yet showing them off is a big no-no. Which is why it's possible to get custom made clothes that'll help cover them up."


translate English day2_gr_9332c4a3:


    pl "So what you're saying is, that coat you're wearing is like a vestment? It doesn't look all that special to me, though..."


translate English day2_gr_799b7bf8:


    gr "Th-This coat was just me asking the bishop for a favor!"


translate English day2_gr_38d0af84:


    gr "I guess you could call it an exception to the rule. It's a little embarrassing..."


translate English day2_gr_08ac5cb4:


    gr "I know most folks around here aren't like me. All you youngsters are so sweet and serious."


translate English day2_gr_559abbf3:


    pl "There's something that's been bugging me for a while now..."


translate English day2_gr_0e2a2913:


    pl "How old are you, doc?"


translate English day2_gr_aa0f554e:


    gr "A lady never tells!"


translate English day2_hk_dc3b1159:


    nar "The only sound in the workplace is the mechanical clacking of machinery. Even from a distance, I can tell no one's there."


translate English day2_hk_1df4b5b8:


    nar "Glancing around this desolate place brings to mind memories of the cafeteria, bustling with priests coming and going."


translate English day2_hk_92a93600:


    nar "Apparently, no one wants to deal with any work-related business until after lunch."


translate English day2_hk_5204d35f:


    nar "I remember bumping into that weirdo here yesterday, though even he's nowhere to be seen."


translate English day2_hk_a01f82b7:


    nar "Maybe he's eating lunch at the cafeteria? If so, my respect for him might go up a touch."


translate English day2_hk_72477702:


    nar "He seems to carry a shroud of lonesomeness around him in the midst of all this clamor."


translate English day2_hk_d7b1a5ac:


    nar "Lost in thought, I suddenly feel someone poke my shoulder, catching me off guard."


translate English day2_hk_633e1d13:


    pl "Ack!" with sshake


translate English day2_hk_3246e23e:


    hk "Whoa!" with sshake


translate English day2_hk_4312fdc7:


    nar "I turn to see someone I wasn't expecting. Or rather, the last person I would have imagined being here."


translate English day2_hk_62d8bc62:


    nar "What is the bishop doing in a place like this?"


translate English day2_hk_efe3eae7:


    nar "Once I've calmed down, she laces her fingers together, including the one that poked me, and looks at me with bright amber eyes, blinking two, three times."


translate English day2_hk_8ba605d2:


    pl "D-Don't just sneak up on people! You practically gave me a heart attack!"


translate English day2_hk_ba0fa8e2:


    hk "That's my line... Now, what are you doing here, [na]?"


translate English day2_hk_3eace8d1:


    hk "As nothing more than a trainee, I thought your work ends at noon?"


translate English day2_hk_d4b216fc:


    pl "That's...! Well... Sorry, but..."


translate English day2_hk_6b7af2ad:


    nar "Blue shadows swirl in her eyes as the clouds pass by, obscuring the bright glow of the night sky."


translate English day2_hk_a643b145:


    nar "In this moment, she seems brighter than anything on earth, as if having been blessed with an inextinguishable light."


translate English day2_hk_3a1882d3:


    nar "You could say her eyes are blue, but bathed in this light, they glimmer like amber waves of grain swaying on a plateau."


translate English day2_hk_640651b8:


    nar "Beneath the pitch-black heavens of the polar night, the light from the candle she holds flickers, {w}the gold that fills her eyes swaying alongside it."


translate English day2_hk_cd158e25:


    nar "She's only holding a single candle and yet, perhaps due to how used to the dark my eyes have grown, the glow from the flame seems preternaturally bright."


translate English day2_hk_f67ebffc:


    nar "Encompassed by a golden glow, it has the effect of making her seem even more ethereal than usual."


translate English day2_hk_6e1c9fe4:


    nar "And then she touches me without any warning whatsoever. {w}There's no way I can calm down from that so easily."


translate English day2_hk_b5e11ef4:


    hk "But...?"


translate English day2_hk_c6a8f301:


    pl "But anyone would be scared out of their minds having an important person like you seemingly walk out of the shadows and poke them. {w}Maybe say something first next time!"


translate English day2_hk_6f2a5ff4:


    hk "I did, in fact, do just that."


translate English day2_hk_358c6635:


    pl "Huh? When?!"


translate English day2_hk_b87d7be2:


    hk "We are all united through God, our father who art in Heaven..."


